# MCR 421: Materials Counts (4) - Materials Counts

**Date Posted:** June 22, 2026

## Overview

This query is the final step in the materials count reporting process. It produces report-ready materials counts using the flattened formats table created by MCR 420.

The query is designed to provide annual reporting statistics and may be modified to support changing reporting requirements.

## Notes

Inactive locations and supressed instances are filtered out in MCR418, as are supressed records. Wood locations and suppressed holdingsa re filtered out in this query. 

Any custom reporting should generally occur at this stage rather than modifying the underlying format-classification logic.



## Workflow

MCR 418 (Data Prep)
        ↓
MCR 419 (Primary Formats)
        ↓
MCR 420 (Flattened Formats)
        ↓
MCR 421 (Materials Counts)


## Annual Reporting Process

1. Create the data preparation table using MCR 418.
2. Apply format classifications using MCR 419.
3. Flatten format arrays using MCR 420.
4. Generate final counts using MCR 421.
